research/history/round_summaries/round_0040.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 39 improved the `gated` K128 anchor from `0.149936` to `0.148156` and the whole curve was better from start to finish while still improving late, so the LR branch has not saturated yet. The next single question is whether this gain continues one more small step upward: does `LR=2.4e-3` preserve the healthy curve shape and improve further over the new `2.0e-3` anchor, or does it begin to overdrive the recipe?",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0040.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the same `gated` mainline and continue the learning-rate sweep with one adjacent confirmation step. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge this round by full trajectory shape, not just terminal FVU: if early and mid training remain as smooth as Round 39 and the late descent goes lower than `0.148156`, then the LR optimum is still above the current anchor; if the curve gets noisier, flatter, or regresses, stop the LR branch and lock `2.0e-3` as the mainline setting.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0040.json:23:    "family_name": "gated",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0040.json:25:    "self_review": "This keeps the search on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `lr`. It also follows the stated policy to do one more nearby LR confirmation after a clean improvement, instead of prematurely switching axes or opening a new family. The main risk is overshooting into instability, but that is precisely the single question this round is meant to answer.",
