research/history/round_summaries/round_0034.json:20:    "summary": "The optimizer branch already failed once (`adam` at the matched LR), and the follow-up Adam LR callback was policy-rejected, so the next valid mainline move is to return to the proven `signum` anchor and test one loss-side variable. Keep architecture, K, EF, optimizer, and LR fixed, and introduce a small `auxk_alpha` rather than a large perturbation. Evaluate the whole trajectory: if early progress is steadier and the run finishes at or below the current `0.149866`, loss shaping is worth keeping in play; if the curve is uniformly worse or distorts convergence, drop aux loss and preserve the plain gated recipe.",
