research/history/round_summaries/round_0042.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` family and return to the `signum` anchor at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, with the same runtime knobs pinned, and change only the loss-side variable `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0`. Judge this run by curve shape as well as terminal FVU: if dropping aux yields a smoother or lower full trajectory than the current `0.148156` anchor, then the stronger LR has made the auxiliary term unnecessary or harmful; if it regresses or destabilizes training, keep the default aux loss and move on to preprocess.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0178.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_gated_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0178.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and the gated selector only changes which residual dictionary atoms `b_i` are activated and with what coefficients. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export the trunk factors and residual dictionary as static vector libraries, then run `trunk branch + gated sparse selection + weighted lookup-sum` online. The architectural question is whether dropping the soft-codebook branch but using a gated residual selector yields a better low-cost tradeoff than the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. Selection cost should remain within the feasible regime at `EF=2`, so this probe should produce a real training signal rather than another fast policy reject.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0178.json:20:    "summary": "Probe `lowrank_gated_residual` as the one matched architecture change. It is LUTurbo-exportable (`\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`) through a static low-rank trunk plus static residual dictionary, and it should give a real low-EF signal about whether gated residual selection is worth continuing once the soft-codebook branch is removed.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0178.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_gated_residual",
