research/history/round_summaries/round_0178.json:51:      "`lowrank_gated_residual` is LUTurbo `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`: decode is still a finite weighted sum over a static low-rank trunk plus a static residual dictionary; gating only affects selector-side scoring.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0178.json:52:      "This is a useful matched probe because it is likely budget-feasible at `EF=2`, unlike routed/bucketed two-stage variants, and it tests whether the soft-codebook branch is actually necessary in the current low-cost regime.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0178.json:57:      "If `lowrank_gated_residual` trails the mainline on FVU and/or slows tokens_per_sec without a compensating benefit, mark the family as not worth continuing in the low-EF feasible regime."
