research/history/round_summaries/round_0178.json:77:    "description": "Probe `lowrank_gated_residual` as the one matched architecture change. It is LUTurbo-exportable (`\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`) through a static low-rank trunk plus static residual dictionary, and it should give a real low-EF signal about whether gated residual selection is worth continuing once the soft-codebook branch is removed.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_gated_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; the gate only changes how residual coefficients are selected, not the exported decoder basis. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual vector library, with the gate absorbed entirely into online coefficient/selection logic. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost stays within the `\u2264 1.5\u00d7h\u00d7n` hard budget and remains below the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. The single question is whether this simpler low-rank gated selector is intrinsically strong enough in the current low-EF deployable regime to justify any later follow-up, or whether the mainline\u2019s soft-codebook plus second stage is clearly necessary.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:20:    "summary": "Run one valid matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_residual` while keeping the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a cheaper single-stage low-rank gated architecture is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_gated_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe fields that caused recent policy confusion. `lowrank_gated_residual` is the highest-value remaining matched probe because it preserves LUTurbo exportability, stays within the EF=2 selection-cost budget, and tests whether a simpler one-stage low-rank selector can recover more quality than plain `lowrank_residual` without paying the full mainline cost. The main risk is that the added gate branch may not close enough of the FVU gap to justify even its moderate extra runtime.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:30:        "value": "lowrank_gated_residual"
