research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:7:  "family_name": "gated",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 44 cleanly reproduced the Hadamard-enabled `gated` improvement at `K=128`, so that preprocess gain is now stable enough to treat as the operative recipe rather than a one-off. The next single question is therefore K transfer under the improved recipe: if we keep `gated`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EF=12`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed and step down only to `K=96`, does the stronger recipe preserve or extend `gated`'s advantage at the next lower support where online cost is meaningfully lower?",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:20:    "summary": "Adopt the reproduced Hadamard recipe as the current `gated` reference and begin K mapping under that stronger setting. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `K` from `128` to `96`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory as well as the endpoint: if the improved recipe yields a smooth curve and clearly beats the old `gated@96` control (`0.168960`), then the preprocess gain transfers to a lower-cost point and the family deserves at least one more K step; if it falls back toward the earlier K96 result or loses its curve advantage, keep the improved recipe mainly as a K128 anchor.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:23:    "family_name": "gated",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `k`. The clean Hadamard confirmation in Round 44 closes the recipe-clarification loop, so moving to K is now the most policy-clean next action. The main risk is that the K128 improvement may not transfer downward, but that is precisely the high-value deployment question this round answers.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:30:        "value": "gated"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:79:      "Rounds 43 and 44 jointly established that `USE_HADAMARD=1` is a reproducible improvement for `gated@128` under `signum, LR=2.0e-3`, so this recipe is now stable enough to use for K mapping.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:80:      "Round 45 transfers the improved `gated` recipe to `K=96` to test whether the K128 preprocess gain also buys a better lower-cost point rather than only improving the largest-support anchor."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:83:      "If the improved `gated@96` run beats the old K96 control with a similarly healthy curve, continue down to `K=64` under the same recipe.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0045.json:84:      "If `gated@96` fails to improve materially under the stronger recipe, treat the Hadamard gain as mostly a K128 effect and avoid a long downward K sweep without new evidence."
